article.headline: Winthrop 77, High Point 65
article.story: ROCK HILL, S.C. (AP) -- Torrell Martin scored 16 of his 21 points in the second half to lift top-seeded Winthrop to a 77-65 victory over High Point on Thursday in the semifinals of the Big South Conference tournament. Martin was 4-for-5 from behind the arc in second half, and the Eagles (22-7) went on a 10-0 run with about five minutes remaining to put the game away. High Point (16-13) trailed 57-55 with 4:58, but Winthrop scored 10 unanswered points in just 1:53. The Eagles face the winner of Charleston Southern-Coastal Carolina in the finals on Saturday with a trip to the NCAA tournament on the line. Chris Gaynor added 17 points and Craig Bradshaw had 16 for Winthrop, which will make its eighth trip to the championship game. High Points Mike Jefferson scored a career-high 25 points, including five 3s in the first half. Arizona Reid added 17 points. Winthrop shot 48.3 percent from the floor in the second half.
